Naivasha Prison inmates have received a television, DVD player and digital contentto help them study for the KCSE exam. The equipment and material was donated by Mount Kenya University&rsquo;s School of Education staff and Kenya National Commission for Unesco representative Reuben Nthamburi. Content is from the Kenya Institute for Curriculum Development for inmates enrolled for the test.Nthamburi said this improve the overall performance of learners at the prison. The Kenya National Commission for Unesco has also partnered with the MKU Nakuru campus staff in research titled &lsquo;Effectiveness of Offline Study on Prison Education&rsquo;. The study has been shortlisted for funding by the National Research Fund.